<P style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%" align=center>&nbsp;&nbsp; <font size="7"><u><i><b>BuddyVision</b></i></u></font> </P>
<p><strong><font color="darkblue" size="5" face="Verdana">VIM Visual Instant Messaging</font></strong></p>
<p><font size="5" face="Verdana">- VIM allows for snapshots from the webcam to
be inserted into text automatically. </font></p>
<p><font size="5" face="Verdana">- AIM Direct Connection is used to provide VIM.
It&nbsp; is very challenging to get to run on a machine that is behind a
firewall or has any amount of security. Direct Connection opens up a portal
between two machines.</font></p>
<p><font size="5" face="Verdana">- One key point is that VIM allows you to send
images via a broadcast to multiple people or to a single person. The recipient
need not have a webcam or even BuddyVision installed.</font></p>
